HEADWORD: Proclitic
<hw>Pro*clit"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to lean
forward; <?/ forward + <?/ to lean or incline. Cf.
<er>Enclitic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Gr. Gram.)</fld> <def>Leaning forward;
-- said of certain monosyllabic words which are so closely attached to
the following word as not to have a separate accent.</def>⟦br⟧
